\begin{frame}{A climbing anchor}
\begin{columns}[T]

  \begin{column}{.4\textwidth}
    The rock climbing anchor contains four carabiners (metal oval clips) with gates that
    open and close so that the rope can be clipped into them. 
    The anchor is redundant so that even if one part fails, the climbers don't fall to
    their deaths.
