\begin{frame}{A climbing anchor}
\begin{columns}[T]

  \begin{column}{.4\textwidth}
The carabiner on the left has
    a screw lock, but the three on the right have no locking mechanism. Suppose that each
    of the three has a $10^{-2}$ probability of being accidentally
    opened. What is the probability that
    the whole anchor will fail? Does it matter if the probabilities are independent, and if so, do you think
    they would really be independent?
  \end{column}

